- Motion and feedback rules now account for reduced motion and clarity: shared CSS adds a `prefers-reduced-motion` fallback, [UiAlert.vue](/Users/mhostetler/Source/EBoss/eboss_platform/apps/eboss_web/assets/vue/components/ui/UiAlert.vue) defaults status vs alert semantics by tone, and representative HEEx surfaces use explicit `role`/`aria-live` semantics.

